text.section:
After a hearing or upon agreement by the liability self-insurance group, the commissioner may suspend or revoke the certificate of filing of a liability self-insurance group, impose a civil penalty of up to five thousand dollars ($5,000) per violation on a liability self-insurance group, or both, for:
Violations of this subtitle or administrative regulations adopted thereunder;
Obtaining a certificate of filing by unfair or deceptive means;
Operating in a financially hazardous manner;
Misappropriation, conversion, illegal withholding, or refusal to pay over upon proper demand any moneys that belong to a member, an employee of a member, or a person otherwise entitled thereto by the group or its administrator; or
Violations of Subtitle 12 of this chapter or administrative regulations promulgated pursuant thereto.

The commissioner, in his or her discretion and without advance notice or a hearing thereon, may suspend or revoke the certificate of filing of any liability self-insurance group upon the commencement of the following proceedings:
Receivership;
Conservatorship;
Rehabilitation; or
Other delinquency proceedings.
